Installation:
Sql server for linux:
https://manjaro.site/how-to-install-microsoft-sql-server-2019-on-linux-mint-20/

Ref 2: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/linux/quickstart-install-connect-ubuntu?view=sql-server-ver15
Administrator password: P@ssword
Connect to sql server:
sqlcmd -S localhost -U SA -P 'P@ssword'
List all db: SELECT Name from sys.Databases

Install mssql extension to manage sql server from vscode.
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/tools/visual-studio-code/sql-server-develop-use-vscode?view=sql-server-ver15

Get server name:
SELECT @@SERVERNAME
Get running instance name (service name)
SELECT @@servicename
